DNOS 10.5.6.9 for Powerscale backend introduced a new user, REST_USER
REST_USER has a default password configured.

The switch operating system (DNOS) monitors if the REST_USER password has been changed.
If REST_USER has the default password, the switch reports an error in the output of the command:
show smartfabric validation-errors


OneFS uses the output from the switch to generate celog events.
The OneFS Error is:
Internal-Err(CLUSTER): REST_USER is using the default password.
Cause
Introduction of a new user in DNOS - REST_USER

Resolution
OneFS versions 9.13, 9.10.1.4 and 9.7.1.10

Execute the command isi_config_be_cred on the cluster, this changes the password on the switch, and saves the password on the cluster.

Username: REST_USER

Password: D@ll1234!
For all other versions of OneFS the following commands run from the cluster change the REST_USER password.

INT-A:

curl -k -s -X PUT -d '{"NewPassword": "D@ll1234!"}' 'https://REST_USER:admin@[fdfe:9042:c53d::5eff:fe00:101]/redfish/v1/Dnv/ChangePassword'

INT-B:

curl -k -s -X PUT -d '{"NewPassword": "D@ll1234!"}' 'https://REST_USER:admin@[fda7:e6ee:2e09::5eff:fe00:102]/redfish/v1/Dnv/ChangePassword'
